## 🚀 How to Reproduce
1. Open Splunk Search & Reporting app
2. Run a base search (e.g. `index=_internal sourcetype=splunkd`)
3. Save search as a **Report** and configure scheduling options
4. Create an **Alert** with trigger conditions (real-time or scheduled)
5. Configure **throttling and permissions**
6. Test and validate triggered actions (e.g. email, webhook, log entry)

---

## 📘 Lessons Learned
- Scheduled reports are essential for recurring monitoring & dashboards  
- Alerts require careful tuning to avoid false positives/noise  
- Throttling and permissions give better control of notifications  
- Documentation and recording help showcase technical skills  

